1. Navigation (folders move karna)
pwd → current directory
ls → list files
ls -la → hidden + details
cd foldername → folder open
cd .. → back
cd ~ → home


2. File & Directory Management
touch file.txt → file create
mkdir folder → folder create
rm file.txt → delete file
rm -r folder → delete folder
cp file1 file2 → copy
mv old new → rename/move


3. File Viewing / Editing
cat file.txt → show content
less file.txt → scroll view
head file.txt → top lines
tail file.txt → last lines
nano file.txt → edit simple
vim file.txt → advanced editor


4. Permissions & Ownership
chmod +x file.sh → permission change
chmod 777 file → full access
chown user:file file.txt → owner change


5. User Management
whoami → current user
id → user info
adduser username
passwd username
su username
sudo command


6. Process Management
ps → running processes
top → live processes
htop → better UI (install first)
kill PID
kill -9 PID


7. Networking
ip a → IP address
ping google.com
netstat -tuln
ss -tuln
curl url
wget url


8. Package Management (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt install package
sudo apt remove package


9. Disk & Storage
df -h → disk usage
du -h → folder size
lsblk → disks
mount
umount


10. Archive & Compression
tar -cvf file.tar folder
tar -xvf file.tar
zip file.zip file
unzip file.zip


11. Search & Text Processing
find / -name file.txt
grep "word" file.txt
sort file.txt
uniq file.txt
wc -l file.txt


12. System Info
uname -a
hostname
uptime
free -h
top


13. Shortcuts
clear → screen clean
history → commands history
!! → last command run
ctrl + c → stop
ctrl + z → pause
